title: $A recovers from mixed local jobs data
text:
Fri, Aug 7, 2015, 7:13 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 2 hrs 47 mins $A recovers from mixed local jobs data AAP – 37 minutes ago Print 
The Australian dollar has bounced back from a slightly negative reaction to volatile local employment numbers. 
At 0630 AEST on Friday, the currency was trading at 73.43 US cents, up from 73.30 cents on Thursday. 
The total number of people with jobs rose 38,500 in July, after a rise of 7,000 in June, but the unemployment rate unexpectedly jumped to a six-month high of 6.3 per cent. 
CURRENCY SNAPSHOT AT 0630 AEST ON FRIDAY 
One Australian dollar buys: 
* 73.43 US cents, from 73.30 cents on Thursday 
* 91.60 Japanese yen, from 91.50 yen 
* 67.23 euro cents, from 67.16 euro cents 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session) 
Source: IRESS AAP
